Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.75,0:01:36.09,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Ladies and gentlemen,\ngood evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.12,0:01:39.32,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,When he learned something\nof his mother's past,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.89,0:01:42.49,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...the young man saw in her profile\nthe figure of a woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.70,0:01:48.13,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,However, he is\nstill unaware.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.84,0:01:56.00,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Still unaware of the true identity of the man\nwho brought this look to her face.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.14,0:02:05.10,count fo,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(350,352)}Act 5:\NDo You Love Your Fiancée?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.38,0:02:37.34,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe I'm seeing sights like this\nunderneath the Champs Elysees.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.68,0:02:39.15,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's like a dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.82,0:02:41.98,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps this truly is\nbut a dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.19,0:02:45.45,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,At times, I find myself forced\nto consider that possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.66,0:02:50.49,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, here's an eye-opening question\nfor you. How much did you sink into this?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.83,0:02:52.70,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How much did this dream house\nof yours set you back?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.53,0:02:56.80,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We stopped bothering with hassles\Nlike keeping track of the money...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.90,0:02:58.93,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...halfway through construction.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.91,0:03:02.70,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for that reply.\NIt'll make a great headline.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.88,0:03:10.64,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Where's that music\ncoming from?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.98,0:03:13.32,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,There!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.46,0:03:23.93,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,She's the girl from\nthe opera!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.77,0:03:27.10,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,She's beautiful...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.20,0:03:30.73,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're not gonna try and tell us\Nthat she's artificial, too, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.10,0:03:32.80,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be rude!\NShe's...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.91,0:03:35.84,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,She is a doll\nnamed Haidee.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.11,0:03:42.38,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A poor puppet who still lives, even\Nafter her soul has been stolen away.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.25,0:03:46.08,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Haidee obeys\nmy every whim,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.19,0:03:50.68,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...and should I wish it, would not\nhesitate to take her own life.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.92,0:03:52.15,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're kidding...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.26,0:03:57.22,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be so surprised. This is the Count\nof Monte Cristo we're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.33,0:03:59.42,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He renounced his soul\nages ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.70,0:04:00.89,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Am I wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.23,0:04:03.00,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're going too far,\NBeauchamp!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.80,0:04:08.80,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How else could a man amass a fortune\nlike this in one lifetime?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.01,0:04:11.77,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm afraid... I must agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.88,0:04:13.94,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you all\nacting like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.28,0:04:18.18,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, the Count isn't as cold\na man as you think he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.25,0:04:19.74,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right,\NCount?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.95,0:04:23.91,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I would not know.\NI cannot see myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.16,0:04:35.90,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome to our home.\NI am Haidee.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.00,0:04:37.20,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.24,0:04:42.14,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Who's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.54,0:04:48.38,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He is Ali. Like Haidee, he is\na noble doll that I own.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.62,0:04:53.45,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Haidee, the Viscount\nseems perplexed...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.79,0:04:57.19,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...as to what\nyou are to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.82,0:05:03.28,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I am but a humble twig\nthat allows the Count to bloom.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.90,0:05:09.30,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A graceful girl like her is the twig,\nand the Count is the flower, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.74,0:05:12.50,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Are you happy\nlike this?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.88,0:05:20.14,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I know the joy of making\nthe flowers bloom.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.51,0:05:21.48,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.62,0:05:26.52,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Does my harp's music\nsound gloomy?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.99,0:05:28.04,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.52,0:05:30.68,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The notes of a harp\nare the notes of the heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.69,0:05:34.18,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The strings don't respond\nto a hesitant, timid heart,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.53,0:05:37.46,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...and a tense heart will cause\nthe strings to break.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.73,0:05:42.57,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Being with the Count\nmakes me happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.94,0:05:48.07,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I assumed that you and the Count\nwere in love with one another...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.31,0:05:52.33,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,In love with each other, huh?\NCould you be any more naive?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.81,0:05:54.28,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What's that supposed\nto mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.61,0:05:55.71,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.12,0:05:59.57,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Marriage among aristocrats is just a strategic\nalliance with the goal of cementing fortunes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.99,0:06:03.42,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,In point of fact, that's why Franz\nand Valentine are engaged, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.49,0:06:05.92,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Is that true?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.76,0:06:10.06,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I won't deny it...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.16,0:06:14.96,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Albert? Isn't it the same\nwith you and Eugenie?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.07,0:06:16.43,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I guess...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.67,0:06:21.30,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, love is something that\ndoesn't exist in the privileged class.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.87,0:06:23.71,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How can this be...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.36,0:06:45.02,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter,\NMaximilien?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.13,0:06:47.60,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Is what I said too hard\nto swallow?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.70,0:06:48.47,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.47,0:06:50.56,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Even so, everything I said\nwas the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.00,0:06:54.96,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The only thing that's important to them is\nkeeping their family fortune from shrinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.21,0:06:59.34,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, you two aren't the product of\nlove, you're the product of financial interests.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.51,0:07:00.71,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't be so sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.81,0:07:04.61,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,For my parents at least, they say that\ntheir marriage was out of love.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.85,0:07:09.12,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I find that hard to believe. A notorious\nplayer like General Morcerf?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.22,0:07:11.28,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Are you trying to\ninsult my father?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.93,0:07:15.62,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Seeing you get so mad about it\nmakes it seem even more dubious.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.80,0:07:19.56,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Is there something about your parents\nthat you're feeling guilty about?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.80,0:07:21.89,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.54,0:07:27.06,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why would I feel guilty\nabout anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.37,0:07:28.60,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Beauchamp.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.71,0:07:31.80,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care if you think you're a journalist.\NYou should drop this subject.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.91,0:07:34.51,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what's this? You're clamping\Ndown on freedom of speech now?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.08,0:07:38.57,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"How wretched it all is..."\NIs that not what you are thinking,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.02,0:07:40.82,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...my good\NCaptain Morrel?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.72,0:07:48.28,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,To think that loveless marriages\nare allowed to go unquestioned...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.27,0:07:57.20,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Is something wrong,\NMaximilien?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.54,0:08:02.60,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The people of Paris\nare corrupt!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.11,0:08:05.77,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Maximilien, you're going too far!!\NI demand that you take that back!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.81,0:08:09.30,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I can't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.78,0:08:14.01,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Paris has more than its fair share of honest,\nupright people! Take back what you said!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.22,0:08:16.71,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I can't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.29,0:08:21.45,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Take it back!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.56,0:08:22.58,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.93,0:08:23.90,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it, Albert!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.00,0:08:24.72,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, now...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.83,0:08:25.99,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.63,0:08:29.26,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Viscount Morcerf.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.67,0:08:33.50,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Do you realize what you\nare pointing at me?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.01,0:08:36.84,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I must warn you,\NI am a soldier.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.99,0:08:47.32,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This will not do.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.62,0:08:50.28,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It is unseemly for one party to draw\nhis sword while the other does not.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.69,0:08:51.82,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Count?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.96,0:08:55.26,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It appears to me that each of you\nis steadfast in your opinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.83,0:09:00.09,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,As we are at sea, perhaps we pirates\nshould act the part...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.87,0:09:03.49,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...and have a duel?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.87,0:09:04.86,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A duel?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.97,0:09:07.53,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,On the sea, strength counts\nfor everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.87,0:09:10.67,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He with the better sword arm\nmakes the rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.78,0:09:12.21,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Are you serious?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.31,0:09:14.14,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What are you suggesting, Count?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.45,0:09:22.28,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Come, now is the time to\ndemonstrate your conviction.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.62,0:09:28.42,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Prove to them that you hold your\nparents' marriage to be sacred.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.00,0:09:33.19,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The blade in your hand\nis invincible.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.80,0:09:39.00,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And you, Monsieur?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.24,0:09:43.40,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,All men have a blade\nin their heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.08,0:09:47.10,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The purer the heart,\nthe keener the blade.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.72,0:09:56.71,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The time is high tide, the place is the ship's\nbow, and the weapons are bare blades!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.82,0:09:59.22,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, gentlemen!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.39,0:10:01.76,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see you go at it,\npirate style!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.93,0:10:08.33,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's hard to believe that there are still people in\nthis day and age who'd fight a duel over love...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.03,0:10:12.00,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Is this any time to be joking?!\NThose swords are real!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.10,0:10:16.23,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And the water down there is teeming with\nsharks that are thirsting for human blood!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.51,0:10:20.24,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Count, what are you\ntrying to do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.55,0:10:23.11,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sea voyages are accompanied\nby their own entertainment.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.25,0:10:26.98,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I expect that Monsieur Albert is\Nthirsting for stimulation of this sort.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.02,0:10:33.22,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Let's do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.29,0:10:35.85,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Whenever you're ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.20,0:11:12.19,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Take back\nwhat you said!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.30,0:11:12.89,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I can't!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.00,0:11:13.97,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why, you...!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.21,0:11:23.33,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How about now?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.01,0:11:26.00,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You poor, sad people...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.12,0:11:34.45,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The purer the heart,\nthe keener the blade.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.99,0:11:38.05,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You aren't capable\nof defeating me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.66,0:11:39.75,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.06,0:11:45.12,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Understand this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.46,0:11:49.03,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what you say, no matter\Nhow it is with other families,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.47,0:11:52.34,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...my parents' marriage\nis a sacred bond!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.07,0:11:55.10,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't expect you to turn\ntowards your unarmed side.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.57,0:11:58.34,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I admire your agility.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.01,0:12:04.04,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Nevertheless, the insincere will be\nsmitten by righteous anger!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.82,0:12:11.72,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I won't stand for it!\NI won't!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.82,0:12:14.82,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What in the world's gotten\ninto Maximilien?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.36,0:12:17.33,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I guess he's the\nscrupulous type.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.20,0:12:21.46,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're finished!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.74,0:12:25.10,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you have such disdain\nfor the aristocracy?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.20,0:12:26.73,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's none of\nyour concern!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.84,0:12:28.97,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The hell it isn't!\NTell me why!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.07,0:12:31.13,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, there's something\NI want to ask you, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.48,0:12:34.64,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Is it true that you don't\nlove your fiancée?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.15,0:12:35.91,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Well, l...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.01,0:12:37.48,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I demand an answer!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.72,0:12:40.98,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.42,0:12:45.72,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,As I thought, I can't\nabide by this!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.57,0:12:58.80,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You have lost, Monsieur.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.65,0:13:15.75,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, hold it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.46,0:13:21.55,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Albert!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.37,0:13:27.13,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,- Albert!\N- Don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.23,0:13:28.76,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,There are sharks\ndown there!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.84,0:13:32.17,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This is a nightmare...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.27,0:13:33.76,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.71,0:13:36.80,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This is a dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.38,0:13:40.97,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,All is but a waking dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.69,0:13:56.89,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Albert...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.73,0:13:59.06,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Mother...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.97,0:14:02.43,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I did it because you had that\nlook on your face, Mother...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.44,0:14:13.81,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Count...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.91,0:14:17.21,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,One cannot fight destiny.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.14,0:14:49.94,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm ashamed of myself.\NI can't believe how angry I got.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.48,0:14:54.32,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I can see it clearly.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.55,0:14:59.39,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Within your heart, another side\nof yourself lies dormant.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.13,0:15:05.36,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,At the moment, you are burdened with\na profound sense of apprehension.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.53,0:15:09.16,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,As am I.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.27,0:15:10.50,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You are, Count?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.44,0:15:16.74,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I have need of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.78,0:15:18.97,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Who, me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.65,0:15:23.10,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You and I met\nthat day on Luna.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.65,0:15:27.52,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps you feel that our meeting\nwas a chance encounter.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.32,0:15:32.26,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But in fate, there are\nno coincidences.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.09,0:15:37.65,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Just as that setting sun does so\Naccording to the laws of the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.83,0:15:44.39,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...fate, too, is composed\nof unyielding necessity.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.94,0:15:52.00,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What are you apprehensive\nabout, Count?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.11,0:15:57.78,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It is because a man loves\nthat he laughs, cries, and hates.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.42,0:16:01.25,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Count, what are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.09,0:16:09.08,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My life is much like\nthis miniature garden.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.93,0:16:13.26,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It is a hollow,\nfragile thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.81,0:16:31.01,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,C'mon, Albert, cheer up already.\NMaximilien already apologized, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.72,0:16:33.55,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not mad.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.65,0:16:34.74,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Then why...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.69,0:16:44.03,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don't hang around\nthe Count anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.66,0:16:46.60,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You've been acting\nfunny lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.90,0:16:50.49,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.\NI guess I have.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.37,0:16:54.50,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Something's funny.\NSomething about all this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.97,0:16:58.91,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Up until yesterday, life was one\nuneventful day after another.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.34,0:17:04.01,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It almost feels like something hidden\nis at work behind all this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.98,0:17:10.39,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Destiny... Have you ever thought\nabout fate and stuff like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.59,0:17:15.39,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No. I don't believe\nin that stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.80,0:17:22.13,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How did your mother\nand I meet?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.47,0:17:24.77,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why the sudden interest?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.87,0:17:26.43,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Please, I'd like to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.94,0:17:32.93,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,As I've told you before, your mother and I\nwere married after a storybook courtship.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.65,0:17:39.17,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it was just as your father says.\NWe were lovers.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.32,0:17:49.62,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I've never seen that look\non Mother's face before.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.03,0:17:55.12,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You look like you're delirious\nwith a fever, young master.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.00,0:17:57.90,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you go out\nfor some fresh air?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.50,0:18:00.13,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Make sure you\nclean in here!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.24,0:18:03.61,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.80,0:18:28.79,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Mother, who are you thinking\nabout right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.68,0:18:41.34,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How far will the ship sail,\NI wonder?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.68,0:18:46.58,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,There is no\nturning back now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.50,0:19:06.84,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I see... You hope to expand your business\nventures to include Paris, as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.17,0:19:12.37,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I can think of no stronger backer to\Nhave than yourself, General Morcerf.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.71,0:19:18.48,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You do me a great honor,\NMonte Cristo.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.62,0:19:22.75,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I take it that you already\nhave a plan of action.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.12,0:19:26.85,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Please feel free to call on me\nshould you have any need at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.57,0:19:38.70,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He seems to be\nquite powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.84,0:19:43.33,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The crest of the Danglars family can\nbe seen here and there around town.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.51,0:19:47.38,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He has no idea that the Count\nis keeping a close eye on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.48,0:19:49.34,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Talk about conceited.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.58,0:19:53.35,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Waving a sword around\nin anger like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.79,0:19:55.72,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You really are hopeless,\nyou know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.56,0:20:05.36,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me, what kind of relationship\ndo you and I have?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.40,0:20:08.06,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What brought this on?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.23,0:20:10.36,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Something that\NMaximilien said.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.70,0:20:14.76,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"Is it true that you don't\nlove your fiancée?"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.94,0:20:17.27,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.84,0:20:20.68,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Do you, Albert?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.28,0:20:29.15,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You and I... are childhood\nfriends, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.06,0:20:33.22,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You and Franz\nhave changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.49,0:20:36.15,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,In the old days, the three of us\nwould always have fun together.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.96,0:20:39.56,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But now, the two of you sneak off\non trips by yourselves...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.10,0:20:42.83,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Everybody is changing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.97,0:20:47.84,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know why Maximilien\nwas so angry?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.74,0:20:51.94,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You honestly don't know?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.58,0:20:55.01,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Well, if you say so.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.11,0:20:56.64,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What's that supposed\nto mean?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.45,0:21:01.78,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I guess no one can do anything\nto stop it...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.19,0:21:05.21,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...when two people have feelings\nfor each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.59,0:21:10.42,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't mean to keep\nyou waiting, Eugenie.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.63,0:21:14.43,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. It took a long time\nto get ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.77,0:21:15.82,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.93,0:21:20.00,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my. Albert, is something the matter?\NYou look so grim.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.08,0:21:25.44,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Stay safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.54,0:21:27.81,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Albert!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.38,0:21:30.14,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Albert!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.18,0:23:15.18,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,She and her father.\NAnd her mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.65,0:23:18.18,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The specter of uncertainty sneaks up on\nthem through their conflicting emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.72,0:23:20.99,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Next time on Gankutsuou,\NThe Count of Monte Cristo, Act 6:
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.46,0:23:21.72,count fo,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(350,352)}Act 6:\NHer Melancholy, My Melancholy
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.10,0:23:23.26,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,..."Her Melancholy,\NMy Melancholy."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.36,0:23:25.76,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Bide your time,\nand hold out hope!
